The Bauchi House of Assembly has approved Governor Bala Mohammed’s request to appoint 10 special advisers. The House gave the approval after it resumed sitting, yesterday, from its indefinite adjournment, by Speaker Abubakar Suleman. Minority Leader Bakoji Bobbo (PDP, Misau) read the correspondence from the office of the Secretary to the State Government on the floor seeking approval for the appointment of 10 special advisers. Moving a motion for the approval afterwards, he said Sections 1 and 6 of the Nigerian Constitution permitted the governor to appoint as many advisers to assist him. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE He added that Governor Bala Abdulkadir Mohammed had called on members of the 9th Assembly to be committed on provision of laws that will provide dividends of democracy to the citizens of the state.  Now that Bala has won We’ll checkmate Gov Ayade in C/River - Speaker non payment of salary:Bauchi legislators summon Account General Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin